archetypes.name: Limits to Success (Archetype)
archetypes.rationale: The model shows a reinforcing growth loop of contributors progressing to core developers, but this growth is limited by developer turnover, creating a classic limits to success pattern where growth eventually hits constraints.

variables.name: Project Attractiveness
variables.rationale: To represent the factor that drives initial contributor growth and eventually becomes constrained

variables.name: Workload Pressure
variables.rationale: To represent the increasing burden on core developers that leads to turnover

connections.rationale: More core developers create coordination complexity and workload
High workload pressure increases turnover rate
High workload makes the project less attractive to new contributors

archetypes.name: Shifting the Burden (Archetype)
archetypes.rationale: The model suggests potential reliance on explicit documentation as a quick fix for knowledge loss, while the more fundamental solution of mentorship may be underutilized, representing a shifting the burden pattern.

variables.name: Knowledge Retention
variables.rationale: To represent the accumulated organizational knowledge that affects project sustainability

variables.name: Quick Fix Pressure
variables.rationale: To represent the urgency driving preference for quick documentation over mentorship

connections.rationale: Documentation provides quick but superficial knowledge transfer
High turnover creates pressure for quick solutions
